Scope of this license
---------------------

The MIT License above applies to all files in this repository — the
TypeScript SDK (`sdk/`), React bindings (`react/`), MCP server reference
(`mcp/`), runnable examples (`examples/`), install scripts (`install/`),
public documentation (`docs/`), scaffolder (`create-arcflow/`), tooling
(`scripts/`), and all top-level Markdown reference files.

The ArcFlow Core runtime binary itself — distributed as `arcflow`,
`arcflow-daemon`, `arcflow-mcp`, and the language-binding shared libraries
downloaded by `install/install.sh` from GitHub Releases — is NOT covered
by this MIT license. The Core runtime is a proprietary product of OZ Global
Inc., distributed free-to-use under the terms in LICENSE-CORE.md.

The split is analogous to NVIDIA's CUDA samples (open, MIT-style) versus
the CUDA Toolkit (proprietary, free-to-use): build with ArcFlow freely,
including commercial use, within the Free Use Limits documented at
oz.com/pricing.

  - This repo's contents:                MIT (above)
  - ArcFlow Core runtime binary:         see LICENSE-CORE.md
  - Plain-English Q&A:                   see LICENSE-FAQ.md
